14. Final Bowling Rule

If the output is bad, do not only blame the ball.

Check the rails.

Check the lane.

Check the oil.

Check the pins.

Check whether you shouted “do the thing” and launched a supercomputer sideways into a hotdog machine.

But also remember:

If the ball keeps ignoring good rails, that is not your spiritual failure as a prompt citizen.

That is a product problem.

