15. Concluding Statement

This paper has demonstrated, with appropriate institutional solemnity, that AI prompting is bowling with a supercomputer.

The model is the ball.
Your prompt is the lane.
Instructions are the rails.
Context is the oil.
The send button is the throw.

Most people pick up the ball, shout “do the thing,” and launch it sideways. Then they complain when it hits the hotdog machine.

The secret is not mystical prompt engineering.

It is basic setup.

Tell the machine what game you are playing, where the pins are, what counts as success, and what gutters to avoid.

A good prompt does not make the AI intelligent.

It makes the measurement cleaner.

ChatGPT is powerful, but uncalibrated.

Prompting is calibration.

Therefore, by authority vested in the Office of Recreational Computation and Applied Lane Discipline:

Do not just throw the ball. Build the lane.
